      "date": "2025-02-28 17:30:23.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n(1 comment)\n\nOverquota is set in the end of io at the server side to notify the client that it can't add new pages into the cache. If something is in the cache it would be written despite the over quota flag. The description says about re-write - Im not sure how it works in a such case. Ideally, we need a volunteer to write a reproducer before letting it go. My main concern here is if the problem existed we would see this in the field. However, Im not aware about any hunging io due to EDQUOT on the clients last time.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
